#!/usr/bin/env Rscript
# =============================================================================
#
#  SLAMseq Analysis Pipeline — PANC-1 CDK12/13 Inhibition (THZ531)
#
#  Sections:
#    0.  Configuration & global helpers
#    1.  Alleyoop QC (mapping rate, T>C rates, substitution heatmap)
#    2.  Count matrix construction from slamdunk tabular files
#    3.  Extended QC of count matrices
#    4.  DESeq2 differential expression (steady-state and nascent)
#    5.  GO enrichment + Venn diagrams + 4-way pathway analysis
#    6.  Nascent transcript subgrouping
#    7.  Gene group enrichment (volcano overlays + Fisher OR)
#    8.  TF target analysis (DoRothEA)
#    9.  ATAC-seq metaplots at TSS
#   10.  Gene regulatory network (PANDA)
#
#  Output: PNG (300 dpi) + TIFF (300 dpi, LZW) sized for Word A4 / 2.5 cm margins
#
#  PERFORMANCE CHANGES (vs original):
#    - TX_MAP is built once then cached as tx_map_cache.rds; subsequent runs
#      load it in ~2 s instead of 2-5 min.
#    - build_tx_map() uses feature.type + colnames filtering so only transcript
#      rows and three columns are parsed from the GTF on the first run.
#    - Section 1 file-reading loops (mutation rates, overall rates, read
#      positions) run in parallel via parallel::mclapply (Unix) or a PSOCK
#      cluster (Windows).  NCORES is capped at 4 or detectCores()-1.
#
# =============================================================================

